> These satisfying snacks are perfect for any mealtime or gathering! We're sending flaky, savory empanadas filled with seasoned chicken thighs and veggies and mini beef franks wrapped in bagel dough. All you have to do is bake them and share! In our humble opinion, everything's better with dips, so serve with your favorite condiments (we strongly recommend sour cream for the empanadas!).

> Keep refrigerated until ready to eat; best if used within 7 days.

== Empanadas ==

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 375 degrees. Place the @Maspanadas Chicken Empanadas{9%piece} on a lightly greased #baking sheet{}. Bake on middle rack, flipping halfway through, until golden brown, ~{15-18%minutes}.

> Oven times may vary.

Alternatively, use an #air fryer{}: Coat an #air fryer basket{} with nonstick cooking spray. Arrange empanadas side by side in basket (you may have to work in batches). Air fry at 375 degrees until golden brown, ~{8-10%minutes}.

== Bagel Dogs ==

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Line a baking sheet with #parchment paper{}. Remove plastic and place @Beef Bagel Dogs{12%piece} on prepared sheet; bake on middle rack until golden brown, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> Oven times may vary.

Alternatively, use a #microwave{}: Microwave bagel dogs on a microwave-safe #plate{} until cooked through, ~{30%seconds} for 4 bagel dogs and ~{75%seconds} for 12 bagel dogs. Do not overheat.